 The Sea 

 of Faith/ Was once, too, at the full and round earths 

 shore/ Lay like the folds of a bright girdle furled./ 

 But now I only hear/ Its melancholy, long, withdrawing 

 roar,/ Retreating, to the breath/ Of the night-wind, down 

 the vast edges drear/ And naked shingles of the world. 

